news_header: In September, the number of bankruptcies decreased compared to the previous year.
news_text: In September, Statistics Finland reported that 274 bankruptcies were filed, which is 36 fewer than the same month last year. The total number of employees in bankruptcy companies was 1,218, a decrease of 30 from the previous year. The highest number of bankruptcy applications came from the service and construction sectors, with 54 construction companies and 36 trade companies filing for bankruptcy.
